  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "OSEK supports two scheduling policy"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Full preemptive scheduling",
        "Non preemptive scheduling"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Non preemptive scheduling"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below is the example for Non preemptive scheduling,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T1 - High Priority - Non-Preemptive"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T2 - Low Priority - Non-Preemptive"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T1 activates when Task T2 is in running state, even though Task T1 has high priority it has to wait till Task T2 is suspended (Since Task T2 is a non-preemptive task)"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/3.%20OSEK%20Scheduling%20policy/image-2023-5-6_14-26-19.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/3. OSEK Scheduling policy/image-2023-5-6_14-26-19.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Preemptive scheduling"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below is the example for Preemptive scheduling,"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T1 - High Priority - Preemptive"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T2 - Low Priority - Preemptive"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In this case, When Task T1 is activated, it preempts the Task T2 which is still running (Since Task T2 is preemptive)"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/3.%20OSEK%20Scheduling%20policy/image-2023-5-6_16-2-43.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/3. OSEK Scheduling policy/image-2023-5-6_16-2-43.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "GetResource or Lock ISRs",
      "content": "In the case of a full preemptive system, the user shall constantly expect preemption of the running task. If a task fragment shall not be preempted, this can be achieved by blocking the scheduler temporarily via the system service GetResource or Lock interrupts"
    }
  ],
